                 </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>Flee, maintain silence, live a life of contemplative quiet.These are the roots of being without sin and justice.</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p> Partially preserved. Crosses with arrays in the angles mark the beginning and the end of the text. The inscription is identified with a saying of Arsenios from the Apophegmata Patrum (PG 65, 88β)(<bibl><ptr target="#Sacopoulo1966"/>,<citedRange> 97</citedRange></bibl>).</p>  
                
